  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The commissioner which came, they were always very high-positioned people, all very high-positioned officers, army officers or something like this.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So he took them to his office, kept them for a few hours.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They came out, all of them drunk, but not Schindler.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So when they came down to see us, they didn't see us like they should see us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this was done, and it took place many times.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, this is the most dramatic part of Schindler's story.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like we went to, to Gross Rosen, the older women were sent to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And these [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] women were sent, like we, together with thousands of others from Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in-- when they arrived in Auschwitz, what was Auschwitz, everybody knows, even you at the time, the commanding officer of Auschwitz, maybe he knew that he can get something from Schindler.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And maybe that he was just a devil like he was, he told, almost immediately, he let Schindler know he's accepting the order from Berlin that 300 women have, have to be brought to Brunnlitz to, to Schlindler.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he insists that the 300 women he will decide who they are and not Schindler.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then began their big struggle because Schindler told officially or wrote officially or was talking to Berlin that these are the most capable, professional, and whatever you say for, for his purposes and his factory.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He cannot accept just 300-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] not-- not-- not the right women he wants.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So he needs to snow them, and he didn't succeed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't remember exactly, but it took some weeks.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
